WEBVTT

00:02:57.960 --> 00:03:01.200
I naturally gravitated
towards the study of trauma.

00:03:02.480 --> 00:03:05.936
And while sitting in class learning
about post-traumatic stress disorder,

00:03:05.960 --> 00:03:07.560
or PTSD for short,

00:03:08.320 --> 00:03:12.016
my mission to help service members
who suffered like my grandfather

00:03:12.040 --> 00:03:13.480
began to take form.

00:03:15.160 --> 00:03:17.816
We've had various names
for post-traumatic stress

00:03:17.840 --> 00:03:19.440
throughout the history of war:

00:03:20.480 --> 00:03:21.840
homesickness,

00:03:22.400 --> 00:03:23.680
soldier's heart,

00:03:24.600 --> 00:03:25.800
shell shock,

00:03:26.640 --> 00:03:28.720
thousand-yard stare, for instance.

00:03:29.760 --> 00:03:33.416
And while I was pursuing my degree,
a new war was raging,